You're out of your mind.

24:33.098 --> 24:36.476
Accept the blame or Josie's gonnapay the price for what you did.

24:37.019 --> 24:39.897
Look, your doctor said it.You love her too much.

24:40.522 --> 24:42.983
So prove it. Protect her.

24:44.735 --> 24:47.446
You're right. That is my problem.

24:47.529 --> 24:51.074
I've always loved hermore than she loves me.

24:52.492 --> 24:57.122
I realize that now,and I have to stop putting her first.

25:03.420 --> 25:05.839
So, you're the onewith the decision to make, Poppy.

25:06.924 --> 25:08.300
It all depends on you.

25:18.477 --> 25:22.105
You've been white-hot since day oneto prove Warren innocent.

25:22.189 --> 25:24.608
His father's dead... in your house.

25:24.691 --> 25:28.278
The bar got raided, Cydie got arrested,Ingram is sleeping in your guest room.

25:28.362 --> 25:30.322
Why are you takingyour foot off the gas now?

25:30.405 --> 25:33.784
Josie is a victim too, just like Warren,because of her sister.

25:33.867 --> 25:35.577
She won't make it in jail, Des.

25:35.994 --> 25:38.205
Your job is done.You did this to find the truth--

25:38.288 --> 25:39.498
I did this...

25:41.667 --> 25:43.961
to be able to put my headon my pillow at night.

25:45.504 --> 25:49.633
Since I was nine, Mama diedand I went to live with Miss Shirley...

25:50.634 --> 25:52.219
that's all I have ever wanted,

25:52.302 --> 25:56.014
was to be able to put my head on my pillowat night and rest easy.

25:57.808 --> 25:59.810
Warren brought back the unrest.

25:59.893 --> 26:03.605
And it will be the same thingall over again if I send Josie to prison.

26:08.485 --> 26:11.488
I know you're hurting. I can see it.

26:12.114 --> 26:15.826
But you are the only onewho can decide what to do.

26:17.995 --> 26:19.454
And whatever that is...

26:20.831 --> 26:22.207
you better be certain.

27:07.711 --> 27:08.795
When I was growing up,

27:08.879 --> 27:13.300
my mother had a framed quoteon our kitchen counter.

27:13.759 --> 27:15.969
<i>I took it with me when I left home.</i>

27:16.845 --> 27:21.183
<i>Subconsciously, it might have playeda role in my becoming a journalist.</i>

27:21.266 --> 27:25.479
"I am for truth, no matter who tells it.

27:25.938 --> 27:30.776
I'm for justice,no matter who it's for or against."

27:32.110 --> 27:33.362
Malcolm X.

27:35.405 --> 27:38.116
Problem is brother Malcolm never saidwhat you're supposed to do

27:38.200 --> 27:41.537
when truth and justice don't line up.

27:41.620 --> 27:43.372
<i>For a moment, imagine this:</i>

27:43.455 --> 27:47.918
<i>You toss a pebble withoutmuch thought or care into the ocean.</i>

27:48.335 --> 27:52.506
<i>You move on as the ripple effectfrom that tossed stone</i>

27:52.923 --> 27:56.385
<i>creates a tidal wave on another shore.</i>

27:56.802 --> 28:00.097
<i>This podcast was that wave.</i>

28:00.556 --> 28:05.519
<i>And it was feltin every corner of every life it touched.</i>

28:06.562 --> 28:08.897
<i>It upended... no...</i>

28:09.439 --> 28:13.652
<i>I upended everythingin the pursuit of justice.</i>

28:14.194 --> 28:18.991
<i>"Justice." A word more fluidthan I ever realized.</i>

28:19.074 --> 28:21.243
<i>I did what I had to do.</i>

28:21.702 --> 28:23.412
<i>And now I have to pay the price.</i>

28:23.495 --> 28:28.959
<i>Justice has meant something differentfor everyone involved with this case.</i>

28:29.042 --> 28:31.003
Don't let my mother die alone.

28:31.086 --> 28:34.882
<i>That was true in 1999 and it's true now.</i>

28:37.009 --> 28:41.263
<i>I set forth at the beginningof this series to find answers.</i>

28:41.346 --> 28:42.764
<i>I succeeded.</i>

28:42.848 --> 28:47.895
<i>But at what cost?To the Buhrmans, to the Caves, to myself.</i>

28:50.564 --> 28:53.859
<i>How far would I go to right a wrong?</i>

28:53.942 --> 28:55.777
<i>What would I be willing to lose?</i>

28:55.861 --> 29:01.408
<i>And who am Iif I don't risk it all to make amends?</i>

29:02.784 --> 29:06.246
Friday, May 10th, 4:06 p.m.,Menlo Police Department.

29:06.663 --> 29:09.541
This is the recorded statementof Josephine Buhrman.

29:10.250 --> 29:11.418
Josie.

29:13.212 --> 29:14.838
Could you repeat that louder?

29:14.922 --> 29:16.256
Who killed your father?

29:19.676 --> 29:20.761
My mother.

29:22.387 --> 29:24.139
Your mother, Erin Buhrman?

29:24.681 --> 29:25.682
Yes.

29:26.725 --> 29:28.977
Why did your mother kill your father?

29:29.061 --> 29:30.854
To protect me.

29:32.648 --> 29:34.316
My father...

29:36.109 --> 29:37.277
had been...

29:38.237 --> 29:41.156
sexually abusing me for years.

29:43.825 --> 29:46.203
My mother... She found my diary.

29:48.956 --> 29:50.499
She read about it and...

29:51.208 --> 29:53.961
she just wanted to protect me.

29:55.587 --> 29:56.964
What did you do?

29:57.464 --> 30:02.386
There was this old oak tree,it's a very special place for us.

30:02.469 --> 30:06.348
Lanie and I went to go dig up thistime capsule from when we were little kids

30:06.431 --> 30:10.269
and instead we found that.

30:11.353 --> 30:15.524
We found her standing over his body.

30:15.607 --> 30:17.109
And she said...

30:17.609 --> 30:19.528
She swore us to secrecy.

30:20.320 --> 30:23.782
We were just scared kids.

30:23.866 --> 30:26.493
We were just little kids.

30:28.954 --> 30:32.541
I thought I told you twoto go back to bed. Hurry.

30:39.089 --> 30:41.133
Why didn't you tell the police this20 years ago?

30:42.217 --> 30:43.844
Because I didn't remember.

30:43.927 --> 30:47.598
Detective, my client has beendiagnosed with recovered memories.

30:47.681 --> 30:49.808
These are memories unconsciously blocked

30:49.892 --> 30:52.519
due to the high level of stressof the event in question.

30:53.270 --> 30:57.107
Recent events around her familyappear to have reactivated them.

30:59.985 --> 31:01.945
And your testimony to the police?

31:03.947 --> 31:05.490
My mother coached me.

31:06.283 --> 31:07.576
<i>Go ahead.</i>

31:10.954 --> 31:11.997
<i>Say it.</i>

31:12.789 --> 31:14.917
<i>Yes, it was Warren.</i>

31:15.000 --> 31:16.001
<i>Warren Cave?</i>

31:17.544 --> 31:18.545
Lanie.

31:21.924 --> 31:23.675
To be perfectly clear,

31:24.259 --> 31:26.845
you did not see Warren Cavego over the fence?

31:29.389 --> 31:30.516
No.

31:31.266 --> 31:35.562
So your testimony about Warren Cave20 years ago was false?

31:38.315 --> 31:39.316
Yes.

31:48.075 --> 31:49.326
Open 32.

31:50.452 --> 31:52.204
Let's go, Cave. You're free.

32:10.806 --> 32:15.269
<i>Nineteen years ago,I wrote about Warren Cave.</i>

32:16.270 --> 32:18.689
<i>Nineteen years ago,I saw nothing but race.</i>

32:18.772 --> 32:20.274
<i>Mine and his.</i>

32:29.992 --> 32:32.411
<i>His life, my life,</i>

32:32.828 --> 32:35.581
<i>viewed solely through the prism of race.</i>

32:38.125 --> 32:39.334
How do you go on

32:39.418 --> 32:42.963
when the truth that catches you...

32:44.256 --> 32:46.466
irrevocably scars your soul?

32:49.761 --> 32:53.348
<i>How do you rekindle that spark for life</i>

32:53.432 --> 32:57.227
<i>when fate extinguished it years ago?</i>

33:31.553 --> 33:35.682
How do you find the will to press forward

33:35.766 --> 33:38.519
when you don't even knowwhat you're pressing towards?

34:10.967 --> 34:12.219
Hi, Mom.

34:13.929 --> 34:14.929
It's me.

34:42.331 --> 34:43.375
I...

34:45.627 --> 34:48.255
love you too.

35:13.488 --> 35:15.574
If I'm for justice,

35:15.991 --> 35:19.578
no matter who it's for or against,

35:20.454 --> 35:25.250
has justice, in this case,truly been served?

35:36.428 --> 35:38.138
So, are you still planning on staying?

35:39.348 --> 35:40.349
I'd like to.

35:42.601 --> 35:44.269
You're all I've got left.

35:47.773 --> 35:51.235
Do you remember these? These little rings.

35:51.318 --> 35:53.779
They made me feel close to youall these years.

36:03.372 --> 36:06.542
I thought after 20 yearsI finally understood Mom.

36:06.959 --> 36:10.504
That she was trying,trying to be a good mother...

36:12.714 --> 36:15.926
but she was going totell Poppy everything, wasn't she?

36:19.137 --> 36:20.848
The pressure just got to her.

36:22.599 --> 36:26.603
That's why you gave her the pills. For me.

36:32.192 --> 36:36.029
Yes, I mean, everything I do is for you.

36:37.239 --> 36:38.490
Always.

36:40.158 --> 36:43.036
I love you more than you love me,remember?

36:53.338 --> 36:55.799
You're right, but it's impossible, Lanie.

36:56.550 --> 36:57.843
You're too sick.

36:58.677 --> 36:59.970
Poppy was right.

37:01.138 --> 37:02.139
Lanie Dunn?

37:05.642 --> 37:06.643
Josie.

37:06.727 --> 37:08.687
You're under arrestfor the murder of Erin Buhrman.

37:08.770 --> 37:10.272
-Wait. Josie.-Hands behind your back.

37:10.355 --> 37:11.607
Josie. Josie.

37:12.608 --> 37:13.609
Josie!

37:14.401 --> 37:16.028
<i>So, is this justice?</i>

37:16.111 --> 37:20.282
<i>Did I do more harm than goodwith this journey into the past?</i>

37:20.824 --> 37:22.242
For that one...

37:23.869 --> 37:25.037
Well...

37:26.079 --> 37:29.499
the verdict on me will likely berendered by...

37:31.001 --> 37:32.461
the jury in heaven.

37:40.469 --> 37:42.679
Markus. What are you doing here?

37:43.931 --> 37:45.182
Can I come in?

37:45.641 --> 37:46.683
Yeah.

37:47.184 --> 37:51.522
So, your sister, Desiree,

37:51.605 --> 37:55.108
she told me you're moving to New York.

37:55.192 --> 37:56.401
Is that true?

37:56.485 --> 37:58.570
Yeah, it looks like it. But...

37:58.654 --> 38:00.989
Well, it's probablyfor the best anyway, huh?

38:01.073 --> 38:03.617
That's what Ingram wants,but I don't know.

38:05.577 --> 38:08.205
Well, you know,if it makes it any easier...

38:09.331 --> 38:10.999
I was gonna call this a wrap anyway.

38:11.625 --> 38:12.626
What?

38:13.710 --> 38:15.045
The investigating.

38:16.129 --> 38:19.800
You know,you and me doing our thing together.

38:21.343 --> 38:25.639
You know, when I saw you at the barat your father's party,

38:26.431 --> 38:29.142
standing there looking beautiful,

38:29.977 --> 38:32.187
dripping in all kindsof jewels and money...

38:34.690 --> 38:36.859
I rememberedhow much I used to love you...

38:38.694 --> 38:40.320
how much I still love you.

38:43.615 --> 38:45.075
-Markus.-No.

38:46.869 --> 38:48.871
And I was a knuckleheadwhen we were together.

38:48.954 --> 38:51.915
A young punkwho thought he knew everything.

38:52.916 --> 38:58.172
But I didn't know that a womanwho gives you all of her heart

38:58.672 --> 39:01.300
is a rare and elusive thing.

39:03.510 --> 39:04.887
Well, I know that now.

39:08.682 --> 39:10.058
But now it's too late.

39:12.102 --> 39:13.729
And, you know, Ingram, he a...

39:15.856 --> 39:17.107
he's a solid dude.

39:18.775 --> 39:23.155
And I would never ever do anythingto disrupt your life ever.

39:24.907 --> 39:30.120
So, this is me... out.

39:51.934 --> 39:56.855
<i>On the first episode I told youthis show would be different.</i>

39:56.939 --> 40:00.567
<i>That this show would benot just about Warren Cave,</i>

40:00.651 --> 40:03.237
<i>but also about me.</i>

40:04.738 --> 40:06.448
So the question becomes...

40:08.075 --> 40:11.119
Who am I on this side of the journey?

40:12.496 --> 40:17.042
Have I finally become the real me...

40:19.503 --> 40:22.923
or has the real Poppy Parnellburrowed deep down...

40:24.591 --> 40:26.468
even deeper inside?

40:29.179 --> 40:33.183
Only time, the next challenge,the next adversity,

40:33.267 --> 40:37.896
the next brush with fate will tell.

40:41.233 --> 40:42.860
I am Poppy Parnell.
